            <h2>Great News!</h2>
            <article>
                 <img src="/images/home/reacs-entrance.jpg" alt="REACS Entrance" class="promo-img" />
                <p>
                    <strong>Starting in September 2014 The Rochdale Early Advantage Charter School has opened an annex location.</strong> This location will service Grades K thru 2nd.  Grades 3-5 will be housed in the main building.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The Rochdale Early Advantage Charter (REACS) has been approved for Universal Pre-K. Beginning in September 2014, REACS will have (2) Pre-K classes. Our Pre-K school day starts at 8:00 AM and ends at 2:20 PM. It is located at our Main location.  All parents that are interested can complete an application on the DOE website <a href="http://schools.nyc.gov">schools.nyc.gov</a> or complete a application in person. Students must be (4) years old or turning (4) years old by December 31, 2014. Contact the school for more information.  <a href="/about-us">Read more...</a>
                <p>

            </article>
        </section--><section id="position3"><h2>Special Features</h2>
                <article><p>Beginning from Universal Pre-K, REACS scholars will be exposed to various careers. Guided through a step by step cognitive process of familiarization, scholars will then be able to make timely educational decisions that will provide
                        them with a competitive edge when making college bound choices. <a href="/about-us">Read more...</a></p>

                </article><article class="checklist"><ul>
<li>Special Education(Sp. Ed.) and English as a Second Language (ESL) Scholars eligible to apply.</li>
                        <li>Breakfast, lunch and transportation will be available to eligible scholars.</li>
                        <li>Strong curriculum infused with technology, college-bound and career-focused.</li>
                        <li>Excellent Community Support</li>
                    </ul></article></section><section id="position4"><h2>Get Involved</h2>
                <article><p>REACS need your help to make this a success for both our community and our children. You can make a difference by <a href="/pto">volunteering your time</a> or <a href="/pto">making a donation</a>. Please visit or call us today to find
                        out how you can get involved. <em>Thank You.</em></p>
